Focal keratin expression is common in epithelioid hemangioendothelioma, so vascular markers (CD34, CD31, and Fli-1) are required to differentiate this tumor from metastatic carcinoma.
Focus of necrosis in retroperitoneal leiomyosarcoma.
Epithelioid morphology in retroperitoneal leiomyosarcoma.
Benign fibrous histiocytoma. Storiform arrangement of tumor cells.
Benign fibrous histiocytoma. A circumscribed but noncapsulated fibrohistiocytic dermal proliferation. The overlying epidermis is hyperplastic.
Fascicular architecture in leiomyosarcoma of deep soft tissue.
Leiomyosarcoma arising from a blood vessel.
Fibroma of tendon sheath. Low-power view shows that the tumor is hypocellular and collagenous with clefting or pseudovascular spaces.
Fibroma of tendon sheath. High-power view shows bland spindle and stellate cells embedded in abundant extracellular collagenous matrix.
Fibrosarcoma of bone. Lesions consist of a cellular population of spindle cells that often assumes a herringbone pattern.
Fibrosarcoma of bone. The spindle cells usually show mild nuclear atypia.
Fibrosarcoma of bone. Some low-grade lesions are heavily collagenized. The spindle cells, however, show some mild nuclear atypia.
Malignant fibrous histiocytoma. Most commonly, lesions show pleomorphic, spindle cells in a storiform pattern.
Malignant fibrous histiocytoma. Other lesions show a predominately histiocytic-like pattern with bizarre round cells and highly pleomorphic nuclei.
Osteoma composed of an admixture of woven and lamellar bone deposited in a cortical-type pattern.
